I have read the closed captions.. Can someone explain the girl's perspective a little more? Especially the part sung by Aashima.

I understand that the male parts are depecting the father's hardship and also how much of a show marriages have become , above the sangam of 2 people.
The Wanwun part if I understand correctly is 2 things at the basic lever: the father's emotion and his blessing for his daughter who is now going away.

I don't understand what the girl is trying to convey. Any clarity I will appreciate. Also correct/add to any of the parts I wrote above please.
